    "Extended Summary": {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The input matrix is a 2x2 symmetric matrix M = [ aii aij ; aij ajj ]."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "The output matrix g is a 2x2 anti-symmetric matrix of the form [ c s ; -s c ];  the elements c and s are returned."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Applying the output matrix to the input matrix (as b=g.T M g) results in a matrix with bii=1, provided tr(M) - det(M) >= 1 and floating point issues do not occur. Otherwise, some other valid rotation is returned. When tr(M)==2, also bjj=1."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 0,
      "target": null,
